  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "In https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/altair/p2p-interface.md#sync_committee_contribution_and_proof there's the rule:\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe contribution_and_proof.selection_proof is a valid signature of the contribution.slot by the validator with index contribution_and_proof.aggregator_index\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/altair/validator.md#aggregation-selection looks like the signature should actually be over `SyncCommitteeSigningData(contribution.slot, contribution.subcommittee_index)`.\r\n\r\nHave I mismatched where this signature comes from or did we copy/paste a rule from attestation aggregations and not adjust? :)",
